			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2742428">
									

<p>So then it's even <em>harder</em> to see- the article I linked to there was only considering the lens resolution for Hubble. So it couldn't even see that city block. A telescope on Earth wouldn't have a snowball's chance even in ideal atmospheric conditions. There's a reason those photos I linked to are the first time we've been able to confirm that the landing sites weren't trashed by the takeoff of the return stage.</p>

