														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2742438">
									

<p>It should be pointed out that any earth-based telescope requires a resolution of about .002 arcseconds to see the lander as a <em>dot</em>.</p>
<p>Without compensating for atmospheric distortion, the best resolution you can get on Earth is about .4 arcseconds. With compensation, such as used by the Very Large Telescope, you can get a resolution down to about .030-.060 arcseconds.</p>
<p>Seeing the landers from Earth using hobby/ameateur equipment is basically impossible at our current level of technology.</p>

							</div>

								
					
