														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2742434">
									

<p>I can forgive the size by assuming most of the facility is underground, but I have a bigger problem with this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Airstrip: Single airstrip three kilometres in length on the surface of Mare Imbrium. Vehicles that require the use of the runway are currently only in prototype phases; because of this, the airstrip is primarily used for VTVL landings or take-off.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is just ridiculous. Leaving aside the fact that they're building the runway before they have anything that needs it, which should get someone disciplined (if the prototypes have issues you can't resolve, you've got a great big runway just sitting there), <em>the Moon has no atmosphere</em>.</p>
<p>Therefore, no runway needed. Forward motion cannot be converted into upwards thrust by acting against the atmosphere, vehicles can't decelerate by increasing their drag, and any craft capable of moving forwards is going to be capable of vertical motion.</p>

							</div>

								
