<p>They can decelerate by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lithobraking">applying skids, airbags, or wheels with brakes to the ground</a>, however. Several Moon colony plans have included a landing strip, because it's that much less delta-v you need to worry about, and you could use a rolling cradle or a linear catapult like you find on an aircraft carrier to help launch things back into orbit using less fuel. (Remember that it's not going <em>up</em> that keeps you in orbit, it's going <em>forward</em>)</p>

