					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=455145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252392" alt="Petrograd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=455145)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;" >Petrograd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1486708248 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Feb 2017 06:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2744036">
									

<p>Hmm. I'm not quite buying this. You've got a couple stories you're telling on top of a dossier (mysterious text issues and tyrannical director) which I assumed to be somehow related to each other, but unless I missed something, neither of them are paid off in any way. This is really annoying, because the hints were pretty enticing.</p>
<p>This isn't like the Site in Alabama with the rogue God (I unfortunately don't remember the links, and I'm on my phone), which used an existing story to provide some rich lore from a cool perspective, hidden in a bureaucratic document. This is just big flashing letters saying &quot;Foundation Site: Foul play is afoot!&quot;, and then nothing. You <em>chose</em> to tell a story, there's gotta be at least a scrap of meat at the end.</p>
<p>(Edit: the director thread might have been alright as is if I weren't so in the dark about the other thing, and if that's impacting him, and if any anomalies are involved.)</p>
<p>Also the fake links were annoying as hell, especially when I was trying to figure out the mystery. (And the sound file didn't load, so I might've missed something there.)</p>

							</div>

								
